snippet.textDisplay: I like YouTube because a lot of us deal with situations based off of how we have experienced them, and we see so many unrealistic movies that shape how our love stories play out. People self sabotage, they see the worst, they think it’ll be some fairy tale when in reality each situation is different and sometimes it’s best to both be mature in the situation. If you both break up maturely and feel good about it odds are if it’s meant to be you’ll be back and if it’s not you’ll both be happy and be able to be apart of one another’s lives and families for years to come. I think this is a unique perspective to see a breakup within the public eye with fake media gossip and how it affects real people, their lives and their mental health. They are still trying to do their best to be there for one another discus here there for each other. I’m just happy to see this. There’s never a rush guys if you’re with someone , totally chill out focus on you. If the person loves you and is naturally in your life they will always be there. Jeffree we love and support you guys. Thanks for sharing your story with us even though it’s got to be hard with all the past building up.
